cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on Vehicular Ad-Hoc Networks (VANETs) and their communication protocols, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the threat of jamming attacks in VANETs and proposes a method to estimate the relative speed of RF jammers, which is a security concern. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses the RF Doppler shift to estimate the relative speed of the jammer, which is a concept related to information theory. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a novel algorithm to estimate the relative speed of RF jammers, which can be considered as a control system. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses a pilot-based received signal to estimate the jamming signal and the relative speed between the jammer and receiver, which can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence.
